description:
Kent Chungus, the intrepid redneck historian, recounts the tale of John and Lorena Bobbitt to the best of his knowledge.
Includes an exclusive interview with someone close to the stroy
Kent is back! He recounts the story of Karl Tanzler to The Operator. Sit back for ladies, luddites, and ... liquids.

FROM RUSSIA WITH LOVE
On this episode, Kent takes us to Russia. Also on this episode 9 people try to hike all over Russia ... and they don't make it. Kent has his theories, and we cover them all.
The assassination of Ken Rex McElroy.
Since 1927, the Cecil Hotel has had many mysterious deaths.
Rednecks. Satanists. Chicken coops. The sharing of gay experiences.This one has it all.

Bog bodies.
Like beef jerky, but made our of people.
We rip the lid off the coffin of Edward Theodore Gein.

Boone Helm was the Jeffrey Dahmer of the Desert. The Hannibal Lector of the old west. We're talking about a real wild man.
A man that murdered, pillaged, stole, and ate his way all across the United States and even up into Canada. Always on the horse of his victims, Boone Helm tore through the country like an unstoppable terror.
Saddle up!
The Papin sisters caused one of the most horrific crime scenes to ever play out in France.Cover your eyes. These twins about to go nuts!
Thomas Sweatt was good with his hands. And fire. And killing people. And playing with himself. This should be fun.

Hangings. Decapitations. Electrocutions. Lethal Injections. We’re covering the various ways us humans have ended each other since the inception of capital punishment, but today we’re not focusing on where things went right in those instances. Today...we’re focusing on where things went horribly...horribly wrong. No worries though...either way...Heads are gonna fuckin’ roll.﻿

We’re gonna do a deep dive on a real big murdering turd today. A guy that may...or may not...have been the most sadistic man Baltimore has ever seen. He liked to talk a lot. He liked to eat a lot. He liked to kill a lot. He liked to sometimes join all those things into one and get other people involved whether they realized it or not. You already know who I’m talking about. Today, we’re taking on that lumbering fatass with a special BBQ recipe...Joe Metheny.﻿

A real life Jason V! A hero to many, a bastion of justice, a bludgeon to the depraved - Jason Vukovich has been given the name 'The Alaskan Avenger' by the media and many people throughout the world.Kent pulled out all of the stops on this episode, with not one ... but two surprises for The Operator and for the unwitting audience!To learn more about Jason, or to support him, click the link below: https://linktr.ee/jason.vukovich
A case that needs no introduction, because Kent is tired of doing them ... The Bloody Benders. We are doing the Bloody Benders.
Every been on a plane? Ever flown a plane? Ever stole a commercial airliner and done a barrel roll? Well ... Richard Russell did. We give you ... The Sky King.
He's been called 'Iron Mike,' and 'The Irish Rasputin.' They tried to kill him. But he just wouldn't die.
